chunks.html_content:
You can use this service to:

  • get on the electoral register so you can vote in elections or referendums
  • get on or off the open register
  • update your name, address or nationality by registering again with your new details (if you live in the UK)
chunks.plain_content:
Register to vote
You can use this service to:

  get on the electoral register so you can vote in elections or referendums
  get on or off the open register
  update your name, address or nationality by registering again with your new details (if you live in the UK)

chunks.html_content: This service is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg)
chunks.plain_content:
Register to vote
This service is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg)

chunks.html_content:
You must be aged 16 or over (or 14 or over in Scotland and Wales).

You must also be one of the following:

  • a British citizen
  • an Irish or EU citizen living in the UK
  • a Commonwealth citizen who has permission to enter or stay in the UK, or who does not need permission
  • a citizen of another country living in Scotland or Wales who has permission to enter or stay in the UK, or who does not need permission

Check which elections youre eligible to vote in.

chunks.html_content: You can vote when youre 18 or over. If you live in Scotland or Wales, you can vote in some elections when youre 16 or over - check which elections youre eligible to vote in.
chunks.plain_content:
Register to vote
Who can register
You can vote when youre 18 or over. If you live in Scotland or Wales, you can vote in some elections when youre 16 or over - check which elections youre eligible to vote in.

chunks.html_content: You normally only need to register once - not for every election. Youll need to register again if youve changed your name, address or nationality.
